"{\"uid\": \"cbc.ca-news-canada-montreal-quebec-olympic-stadium-renovations-1.7104546\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Quebec will announce\\u00a0Mondaymorningthat it will indeed replace the roof and technical ring of the Olympic Stadium, according to information obtained by Radio-Canada.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quebec\", \"score\": 0.7374783106253272, \"rank\": 0.35597189524869566, \"text\": \"Quebec\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quebec\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quebec\"}, {\"begin\": 151, \"end\": 163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.9999214864429454, \"rank\": 7.851734576222034e-05, \"text\": \"Radio-Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The work will cost hundreds of millions of dollars, but is not expected to reach the billion-dollar mark.\", \"from\": 166, \"to\": 271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Caroline Proulx, the minister responsible for the file, will unveil a cost estimate during the announcement.\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 272, \"end\": 287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Proulx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caroline Proulx\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Proulx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Proulx\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Previous estimates reported by La Presse were between $750 million and $1 billion.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 413, \"end\": 422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Presse_(Canadian_newspaper)\", \"score\": 0.9945425921603692, \"rank\": 0.005487352252611942, \"text\": \"La Presse\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Presse_(Canadian_newspaper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Presse_(Canadian_newspaper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The project is expected to take four\\u00a0years to complete.\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Necessary renovations include dismantling the existing roof, replacing the technical ring that holds the entire stadium structure together and building a new roof.\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is Montreal's Olympic Stadium worth saving?\", \"from\": 687, \"to\": 730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 690, \"end\": 698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.3413250070582567e-12, \"text\": \"Montreal\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quebec Premier Fran\\u00e7ois Legault said he wanted to make the stadium a \\\"positive symbol\\\" for the province.\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 732, \"end\": 738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quebec\", \"score\": 0.7374783106253272, \"rank\": 0.35597189524869566, \"text\": \"Quebec\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quebec\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quebec\"}, {\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fran\\u00e7ois_Legault\", \"score\": 0.999999882278878, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fran\\u00e7ois Legault\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fran\\u00e7ois_Legault\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fran\\u00e7ois_Legault\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once renovated, the stadium will be able to host events year-round, regardless of weather conditions, which it can not do at the moment.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The government estimates that, once construction is complete, the Olympic Stadium's activities will generate annual revenue ofclose to $150 million- more than double the assessed $68 million it currently brings in.\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 1189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Montreal Mayor\\u00a0Val\\u00e9rie Plante\\u00a0welcomed the news.\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Val\\u00e9rie_Plante\", \"score\": 0.999999985790737, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Val\\u00e9rie Plante\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Val\\u00e9rie_Plante\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Val\\u00e9rie_Plante\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympic Stadium is a jewel of the metropolis, a symbol of the city and a major contributor to the dynamism of Montreal's east end,\\\" she said in a statement from her cabinet.\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1356, \"end\": 1364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.3413250070582567e-12, \"text\": \"Montreal\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We want a lasting solution for the stadium, and its roof.\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1479, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So it's very good news that the government is in a position to announce investments for the renovations it requires.\\\"\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"AlexandreLeduc,MNAforHochelaga-Maisonneuve, said the move is \\\"the only logical choice.\\\"\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The stadium is an\\u00a0architectural jewel and a strong symbol ofHochelagaand Montreal,\\\" he said in a statement.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1762, \"end\": 1770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.3413250070582567e-12, \"text\": \"Montreal\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Radio-Canada sources, the government considered demolishing the stadium.\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.9999214864429454, \"rank\": 7.851734576222034e-05, \"text\": \"Radio-Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An up-to-date assessment of the \\\"cost of inaction\\\" concluded demolition would cost \\\"more than $2 million\\\" along with a loss of revenue from rentals, making it financially unviable.\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 2065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The stadium received private and public investments of over $1.5 billion in recent years.\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to government estimates, the Olympic District has assets worth around $10 billion.\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Demolition would wipe out a large part of these assets and impact the Olympic Park and nearby Metro line.\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If it does not get renovated, the stadium would have to be closed during winter, have the roof dismantled within two years and then be totally demolished.\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Stadium can hold 50,000 spectators.\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By comparison, the Bell Centre has room for just over 21,000 people.\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2580, \"end\": 2591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bell_Centre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bell Centre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bell_Centre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bell_Centre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To justify the renovations in December, Proulx said Quebec was missing out on Taylor Swift's tour \\\"because we currently do not have a stadium able to produce such a show.\\\"\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2683, \"end\": 2689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quebec\", \"score\": 0.7374783106253272, \"rank\": 0.35597189524869566, \"text\": \"Quebec\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quebec\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quebec\"}, {\"begin\": 2709, \"end\": 2721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Swift\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4103068876811252e-25, \"text\": \"Taylor Swift\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Swift\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Swift\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Stadium has been closed since mid-December to allow exploratory work to replace the roof.\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2905, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The decision forced CF Montr\\u00e9al to move its opening match in April to Saputo Stadium.\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 2991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2926, \"end\": 2937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CF_Montr\\u00e9al\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CF Montr\\u00e9al\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CF_Montr\\u00e9al\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CF_Montr\\u00e9al\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Based on reporting by Radio-Canada's S\\u00e9bastien Bovet  Audience Relations, CBCP.O.\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3015, \"end\": 3027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.9999214864429454, \"rank\": 7.851734576222034e-05, \"text\": \"Radio-Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Box 500 Station AToronto, ONCanada, M5W 1E6  Toll-free (Canada only):1-866-306-4636  It is a priority for CBC to create products that are accessible to all in Canada including people with visual, hearing, motor and cognitive challenges.\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3311, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3181, \"end\": 3184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.9999372492164571, \"rank\": 5.7910364058755574e-05, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}, {\"begin\": 3234, \"end\": 3240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999999913598, \"rank\": 8.614088589430984e-12, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Closed Captioning and Described Video is available for many CBC shows offered onCBC Gem.\", \"from\": 3313, \"to\": 3401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3313, \"end\": 3330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Closed_captioning\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"C